STARTUP CANDY COMPANY, a Corporation, v. FEDERAL TRADE COMMISSION. No. 1789. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. March 31, 1939. H. Hartland Halliday, of Salt Lake City, Utah, for petitioner. W. T. Kelley, Chief Counsel, Federal Trade Commission, of Washington, D. C., for respondent.

Before LEWIS and PHILLIPS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Petition to review dismissed at petitioner’s ' costs, on motion of petitioner.
